{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Far too many prosecutors exploit peremptory challenges to create racially unrepresentative juries and win convictions.", "abstract": "Editorial notes Supreme Court is set to hear arguments in case Foster v Chatman, which examines accusations of jury selection bias in 1987 murder trial of black man Timothy Tyrone Foster in Georgia; holds evidence shows peremptory challenge, which allows jurors to be excluded for no stated reason, was used to weed out black jurors and guarantee all-white jury; urges justices to remain vigilant to 'race-neutral' practices being used for racist ends.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "22", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [], "original": "By THE EDITORIAL BOARD", "organization": "THE EDITORIAL BOARD"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/11/02/opinion/excluding-blacks-from-juries.html", "lead_paragraph": "Far too many prosecutors exploit peremptory challenges to create racially unrepresentative juries and win convictions.", "headline": {"print_headline": "Excluding Blacks From Juries", "main": "Excluding Blacks From Juries", "content_kicker": "Editorial", "kicker": "Editorial"}, "_id": "56371cc738f0d829bdc685a6", "word_count": "646", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/11/02/opinion/02mon1/02mon1-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/11/02/opinion/02mon1/02mon1-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 744, "url": "images/2015/11/02/opinion/02mon1/02mon1-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/11/02/opinion/02mon1/02mon1-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "744"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2015/11/02/opinion/02mon1/02mon1-thumbStandard.jpg", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2015/11/02/opinion/02mon1/02mon1-thumbStandard.jpg", "thumbnailwidth": "75", "thumbnailheight": "75"}, "sub